    <stitle>INTERNATIONAL AIR SUSPENSION WITH TAPERED LEAF SPRINGS - LOW FRICTION SPRING LINERS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="2">
        <title>LOW FRICTION SPRING LINERS</title>
        <para>Low friction spring liners are located in the spring brackets, allowing the tapered leaf spring to move
            forward and rearward with a minimum amount of friction, reducing ride harshness.
        </para>
        <para>Low friction spring liners are also installed between the tapered leaf spring assembly and the U-bolt seat
            to reduce fretting.
        </para>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0300111">Figure 11</hotlnk>and
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0300112">Figure 12</hotlnk>
            for assembly detail of 4x2 and 6x4 rear (air and tapered leaf) springs, torque rods, crossmembers, and
            mountings.
        </para>
